article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 83, Nicholls State 69
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Josh Alexander scored 26 points and had seven rebounds to help lead Stephen F. Austin to an 83-69 win over Nicholls State on Saturday. Alexander, who was 10-of-15 from the field, hit three 3-pointers for the Lumberjacks (11-9, 4-6 Southland). Antuane Miller added 20 points and Marcus Clark had 19, including three 3-pointers. The Lumberjacks, who hit 54 percent of their field goals, led 42-25 at the half. Chris Paige scored 15 points and Stefa Blaszczynski had 13 for the Colonels (8-13, 4-6).
